== Crispy Cheesy Fries ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread
out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Halfway through, sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g},
toss to coat, then return to the oven for the remaining time.

== Burgers ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the garlic, @panko breadcrumbs{10%g},
@salt{1/4%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp}, then add the @British beef mince{240%g}.
Season with pepper and mix together with your hands.

Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto a baking tray.

When the chips have 15 mins left, bake the burgers on the middle shelf until
cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Once the burgers are cooked, carefully place the Cheddar on top of the
burgers and return to the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Balsamic Glazed Salad ==

While everything cooks, cut the @tomato{1%medium} into 1cm chunks.

Pop the tomato into a large bowl with the @balsamic glaze{1%tbsp} and
@olive oil{2%tbsp} for the dressing.

Season with salt and pepper, mix together, then set aside.

> TIP: The vinegar in the balsamic helps draw out some of the moisture from
> the tomatoes and seasons them throughout.

== Truffle Mayo ==

In a small bowl, combine the @mayonnaise{64%g} and half the
@truffle zest{2}.

Halve the @glazed burger bun{2}, then pop them into the oven to warm through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

When everything's almost ready, toss the @baby leaf mix{50%g} with the
macerated tomatoes.

Pop the buns onto your plates and spread the truffle mayo over the bases. Top
with a cheesy burger, a handful of balsamic salad, then close with the bun lids.

Serve up your craft burgers with the cheesy chips and remaining salad
alongside.

Sprinkle the remaining truffle zest over the chips to finish. Enjoy!